The paper deals with uncertainty estimation in Bayesian convolutional neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SY). Given that the paper focuses on supervised learning tasks with image datasets, it is most likely to belong to cs.LG and cs.CV. However, since the paper also discusses the use of Bayesian methods and variational inference, it could also be classified under cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.SY.
